---
source: src/graph/mod.rs
assertion: graph centrality commands use FrankenNetworkX and produce deterministic metrics
schema:
  report: ee.graph.centrality_refresh.v1
  score: ee.graph.centrality_score.v1
contracts:
  - centrality metrics use fnx_algorithms PageRank and betweenness centrality
  - no petgraph or hand-rolled graph algorithms in dependency tree
  - same memory links yield stable score ordering with deterministic tie-breaking
  - scores include memoryId, pagerank, and betweenness fields
  - top_pagerank and top_betweenness lists are sorted by respective metric descending
  - empty graph returns EmptyGraph status with zero node/edge counts
  - missing database returns clear Storage error with init repair hint
  - JSON stdout is ee.response.v1 envelope with data containing scores
  - human output formats pagerank and betweenness to 4 decimal places
evidence:
  - CentralityRefreshReport.status
  - CentralityRefreshReport.node_count
  - CentralityRefreshReport.edge_count
  - MemoryCentralityScore.memory_id
  - MemoryCentralityScore.pagerank
  - MemoryCentralityScore.betweenness
  - fnx_algorithms::pagerank_directed
  - fnx_algorithms::betweenness_centrality_directed
